Areyeng Bus service workers affiliated to Numsa have sealed a deal with the City of Tshwane. Numsa spokesperson Phakamile Hlubi-Majola says this is a victory for the workers. #DStv403 PRETORIA - Areyeng Bus service workers affiliated to Numsa have sealed a deal with the City of Tshwane. The union threatened a full-blown strike if the metro failed to meet its demand for a transport allowance. READ: TRT strike | Numsa threatens strike action over travel allowances Last week, workers handed over a memorandum to the local government. Numsa spokesperson Phakamile Hlubi-Majola says this is a victory for the workers. READ: Numsa March | TRT drivers march for travel allowances "We can confirm that we have settled the strike at Xtremetec. At the same time, the threat of a total shutdown of the Areyeng Bus services for the City of Tshwane next week has now been averted," she said. "The agreement we signed goes a long way towards addressing demands our members had."